      "writtenOn": "2020-09-14T07:48:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "IIUC this is a map from a resource URL (e.g. gs://foo/bar) to (path part of) a cached file URL.\n\nIn TLW definition it is up to the TLW server to decide cache file URLs, so I think users of faketlw are not interested in explicitly specifying cached file URLs. I rather think it\u0027s better if users of faketlw can specify the file content, instead of fixed \"This is data file.\".\n\nSo I suggest changing this option to accept map[string][]byte where a key is a resource URL and a value is its file content.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 51,
        "startChar": 22,
        "endLine": 51,
        "endChar": 41
      },
      "revId": "3b5742b9aa3374c186fe4dab09d7d5a9f3c572bd",
